  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q139.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">Fortitude denotes a certain firmness of mind, as stated above ( II-II:123:2 ; I-II:61:3 ): and this firmness of mind is required both in doing good and in enduring evil , especially with regard to</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d19">gift</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q139" target="concept.fortitude_gift" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q139.treated_in.concept.fortitude_gift">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q139.treated_in.concept.fortitude_gift</data>
