  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">Fortitude denotes a certain firmness of mind, as stated above ( II-II:123:2 ; I-II:61:3 ): and this firmness of mind is required both in doing good and in enduring evil , especially with regard to goods or evils that are dif</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d19">gift</data>
</edge>
