  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">serving at the same time a certain fittingness between them. Wherefore he ascribes the fourth beatitude, concerning the hunger and thirst for justice , to the fourth gift , namely fortitude . Yet there is a certain congruity between them, because, as stated ( Article 1 ), fortitude is about difficult things. Now it is very diff</data>
