  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">again of tyrannical governments. Now the end of the Divine Law is that man may adhere to God : wherefore the Divine Law contains precepts both of fortitude and of the other virtues , with a view to directing the mind to God . For this reason it is written ( Deuteronomy 20:3-4 ): "Fear ye them not: because the Lord your God is in the</data>
