  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q140.a002</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.140 a.2 — The precepts of its parts</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.precepts_of_fortitude_parts</data>
  <data key="d12">Precepts of Patience and Perseverance</data>
  <data key="d13">precept</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q140-a002-treated-in-concept-precepts-of-fortitude-parts-st-ii-ii-q140-a002-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q140.a002.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">as are necessary for right living. Now in order to live aright man needs not only the principal virtues , but also the secondary and annexed virtues . Wherefore the Divine Law contains precepts not only about the acts of the principal virtues , but also about the acts of the secondary and annexed virtues .</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d19">precept</data>
